select * from FLOWFILE where failed > 0 or now_running > 0 or scheduled > 0

config.comments: Process date is set by default to ETL_process_date context parameter.

entry.value: SELECT ${pipelines_count} AS pipelines_count, count(CASE WHEN state = 'SCHEDULED' THEN 0 END) AS scheduled, count(CASE WHEN state = 'RUNNING' THEN 0 END) AS now_running, count(CASE WHEN state = 'FAILED' THEN 0 END) AS failed, count(CASE WHEN state = 'COMPLETED' THEN 0 END) AS completed FROM (SELECT state FROM ( SELECT *, max(modified_datetime) OVER (PARTITION BY component_name) AS max_modified_datetime, max(process_date) OVER () AS max_process_date FROM etl_traffic_lights WHERE component_name IN (${pipelines_names}) ) etl_max WHERE modified_datetime = max_modified_datetime AND process_date = max_process_date ) state_summary
